tags: source: From me and my friend from school
angels are chickens with human bodies
summary:
Peter: Angels are chickens with human bodies.
Ned: What?
Peter: Angels are chickens with human bodies, that’s official.
Ned: No,...
body:
Peter: Angels are chickens with human bodies.

Ned: What?

Peter: Angels are chickens with human bodies, that’s official.

Ned: No, they’re not.

Peter: Yea, and I can prove it!

Peter calls to Tony asking: Are angels chickens with human bodies?

Tony: I don’t know??

Peter: He doesn’t know, so it’s not an anwser.

Ned: That random person agreed with you, so I guess it’s true.

Peter: YEAH, LET’S GO SPREAD THE WORD THAT ANGELS ARE CHICKENS WITH HUMAN BODIES!!

Ned: YEAH!

Then they went off and spread the word that “Angels are chickens with human bodies.”

The End

summary: My unpopular opinion: Peter Parker is and will always be straight
body:
My unpopular opinion: Peter Parker is and will always be straight

Go ahead, fight me by listing all the stupidest reasons/examples from comics where he’s hinted to be bisexual/or even remotely gay. It’s not gonna change my opinion, lol. A fan’s headcanon will always be just that: their own fanfic. Doesn’t mean they can’t have that interpretation of that character. Of course they can! BUT.. it’s not cool when you try to force it down our throats.

summary: I never really stopped to consider that the events of Spider-Man: Homecoming took place in September 2016, and Infinity War in...
body:
I never really stopped to consider that the events of Spider-Man: Homecoming took place in September 2016, and Infinity War in summer (June/July) 2018. This means that Tony mentored Peter for nearly 2 years before Peter died in his arms, which is longer than I previously had thought.

So after I finished crying about that again (I will never stop), I got to thinking about the timeline. Skipping over the 5 year jump between IW and Endgame because Peter did not age, doesn’t that mean he should be a senior in Spider-Man: Far From Home, instead of a Junior? Wouldn’t his junior year have been in 2017? Far From Home takes place in the summer of 2023, ostensibly no more than a few weeks after the end of Endgame. Again, factoring in that Peter hasn’t aged and thus has to pick up his high school life where he left off, doesn’t that mean FFH should take place in the summer between his junior and senior year?

I’m not American and may be getting the high school system jumbled up, so if anyone can help me with this timeline conundrum, it would be much appreciated :)
